🌟Push-Ups🌟

One of the more basic moves from my training guide. 💪 I have always found that people who are new to exercising, frequently struggle to understand how to do a push-up properly. ☝️Everyone understands its a simple lowering and raising motion in the "push-up" position, but many people miss the basic cues. ✨Some things I frequently look for are:

1⃣You should be on the tip of your toes or point of your knees and your feet should be together

2⃣Your chest should hit the ground, or be closer to the ground at the bottom of the movement.
 DO NOT sink your hips

3⃣Your elbows should be behind your shoulder when looking from above not straight out from your body. This puts less strain on your shoulder joint

4⃣Go low ⬇️ if you cant almost touch your chest on the ground when you do full push-ups, drop to your knees and go all the way down. ⭐️Remember form is more important than speed ⭐️ ✅WWW.KAYLAITSINES.COM.AU✅
